Note:
BUILD SYSTEM - Multi-File Compilation Orchestration

This file handles build system orchestration and build process management for the compiler.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process build configuration and build system setup
- Handle build target management and build process orchestration
- Manage build optimization and build performance utilities
- Process build validation and build process monitoring

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Build system orchestration is fundamental to compiler operation and project compilation
- Proper build handling ensures efficient compilation process and build management
- Build system utilities support project compilation, dependency resolution, and build optimization

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- BuildContext type for managing multi-file compilation state
- create_build_context for initializing build state
- add_source_file for registering source files to compile
- build_all for iterating files and invoking compilation on each
- build_with_dependencies for topological-order compilation
- Build error tracking and reporting

Dependencies:
- Imports memory_utils.runa for memory allocation
- Imports string_utils.runa for string manipulation
- Imports arena_utils.runa for arena-based allocation
- Imports collections.runa for ArrayList and data structures
- Imports file_utils.runa for file existence checks
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa" as MemoryUtils
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa" as ArenaUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections
Import "compiler/internal/file_utils.runa" as FileUtils
Import "compiler/internal/time_utils.runa" as TimeUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build System Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant BUILD_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant BUILD_FAILURE as Integer is 1
Constant BUILD_PARTIAL as Integer is 2

Constant BUILD_OPT_NONE as Integer is 0
Constant BUILD_OPT_SIZE as Integer is 1
Constant BUILD_OPT_SPEED as Integer is 2
Constant BUILD_OPT_AGGRESSIVE as Integer is 3

Constant BUILD_MAX_SOURCE_FILES as Integer is 4096
Constant BUILD_MAX_ERRORS as Integer is 256

Note: BuildContext memory layout (192 bytes):
Note: offset   0: source_files (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of source file paths
Note: offset   8: output_directory (8 bytes) - Pointer to output directory path string
Note: offset  16: optimization_level (8 bytes) - Optimization level (BUILD_OPT_*)
Note: offset  24: target_triple (8 bytes) - Pointer to target triple string
Note: offset  32: compiled_count (8 bytes) - Number of files successfully compiled
Note: offset  40: error_count (8 bytes) - Number of compilation errors
Note: offset  48: error_messages (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of error message strings
Note: offset  56: arena (8 bytes) - Pointer to arena for build allocations
Note: offset  64: is_verbose (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if verbose output enabled
Note: offset  72: is_incremental (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if incremental build
Note: offset  80: dependency_graph (8 bytes) - Pointer to dependency graph (from dependency_manager)
Note: offset  88: start_time (8 bytes) - Pointer to TimeSpec for build start time
Note: offset  96: end_time (8 bytes) - Pointer to TimeSpec for build end time
Note: offset 104: debug_info (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if debug info enabled
Note: offset 112: warning_level (8 bytes) - Warning level (0=none, 1=some, 2=all)
Note: offset 120: object_files (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of generated object file paths
Note: offset 128: assembly_files (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of generated assembly file paths
Note: offset 136: link_output (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if should link final executable
Note: offset 144: executable_path (8 bytes) - Pointer to final executable output path
Note: offset 152: total_lines (8 bytes) - Total lines compiled across all files
Note: offset 160: is_active (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if build is in progress
Note: offset 168: config (8 bytes) - Pointer to CompilerConfig (from config_manager)
Note: offset 176: cache (8 bytes) - Pointer to CompilationCache (from cache_manager)
Note: offset 184: parallel_count (8 bytes) - Number of parallel compilation threads (0 = sequential)

Constant BUILD_CONTEXT_SIZE as Integer is 192

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build Context Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_build_context" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate the BuildContext structure
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Cannot create build context: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ctx be arena_allocate(arena, BUILD_CONTEXT_SIZE, 8)
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to allocate build context"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Zero out entire structure
    memory_zero(ctx, BUILD_CONTEXT_SIZE)

    Note: Create source files list (ArrayList of pointers, element_size = 8)
    Let source_files be arraylist_create(64, 8, arena)
    If source_files is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to create source files list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 0, source_files)

    Note: Set default output directory to current directory
    Let default_output be string_concat(".", "")
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 8, default_output)

    Note: Set default optimization level
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 16, BUILD_OPT_NONE)

    Note: Set default target triple to empty (will be auto-detected)
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 24, 0)

    Note: Initialize counters
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 32, 0)  Note: compiled_count
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 40, 0)  Note: error_count

    Note: Create error messages list
    Let error_messages be arraylist_create(32, 8, arena)
    If error_messages is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to create error messages list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 48, error_messages)

    Note: Store arena pointer
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 56, arena)

    Note: Default flags
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 64, 0)   Note: is_verbose = false
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 72, 0)   Note: is_incremental = false
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 80, 0)   Note: dependency_graph = null
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 88, 0)   Note: start_time = null
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 96, 0)   Note: end_time = null
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 104, 0)  Note: debug_info = false
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 112, 1)  Note: warning_level = 1 (some warnings)

    Note: Create object files list
    Let object_files be arraylist_create(64, 8, arena)
    If object_files is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to create object files list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 120, object_files)

    Note: Create assembly files list
    Let assembly_files be arraylist_create(64, 8, arena)
    If assembly_files is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to create assembly files list"
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 128, assembly_files)

    Note: Default link and executable settings
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 136, 0)  Note: link_output = false
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 144, 0)  Note: executable_path = null
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 152, 0)  Note: total_lines = 0
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)  Note: is_active = false
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 168, 0)  Note: config = null
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 176, 0)  Note: cache = null
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 184, 0)  Note: parallel_count = 0 (sequential)

    Return ctx
End Process

Process called "destroy_build_context" takes ctx as Integer returns Nothing:
    Note: BuildContext is arena-allocated so individual fields do not need freeing.
    Note: The arena that owns this context will reclaim all memory on arena_destroy.
    Note: However, we must clean up any owned (non-arena) strings.
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Deallocate the default output directory string if it was heap-allocated
    Let output_dir be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 8)
    If output_dir is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(output_dir)
        memory_set_pointer(ctx, 8, 0)
    End If

    Note: Mark context as inactive
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Source File Management
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "add_source_file" takes ctx as Integer, file_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add a source file to the build context
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Cannot add source file: build context is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If file_path is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Cannot add source file: file path is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Verify the file exists before adding
    Let exists be file_exists(file_path)
    If exists is equal to 0:
        Let error_temp be string_concat("[BUILD ERROR] Source file not found: ", file_path)
        Alert error_temp
        deallocate(error_temp)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get the source files list
    Let source_files be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 0)
    If source_files is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Source files list is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check maximum file count
    Let current_count be arraylist_size(source_files)
    If current_count is greater than or equal to BUILD_MAX_SOURCE_FILES:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Maximum source file count exceeded"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Duplicate the file path string so the build context owns it
    Let path_copy be string_duplicate(file_path)
    If path_copy is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to duplicate file path string"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add the duplicated path pointer to the ArrayList
    Let result be arraylist_add(source_files, path_copy)
    If result is equal to 0:
        deallocate(path_copy)
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to add source file to list"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_verbose be memory_get_integer(ctx, 64)
    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
        Let msg be string_concat("[BUILD] Added source file: ", file_path)
        Display msg
        deallocate(msg)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "get_source_file_count" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the number of source files registered in the build context
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_files be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 0)
    If source_files is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return arraylist_size(source_files)
End Process

Process called "get_source_file" takes ctx as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the source file path at the given index, or 0 if invalid
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_files be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 0)
    If source_files is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be arraylist_size(source_files)
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to count:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return arraylist_get(source_files, index)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build Configuration
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "build_set_output_directory" takes ctx as Integer, dir_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the output directory for compilation artifacts
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If dir_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Free old output directory
    Let old_dir be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 8)
    If old_dir is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(old_dir)
    End If

    Let new_dir be string_duplicate(dir_path)
    If new_dir is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to duplicate output directory path"
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 8, new_dir)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_optimization_level" takes ctx as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the optimization level for compilation
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If level is less than BUILD_OPT_NONE:
        Return 0
    End If
    If level is greater than BUILD_OPT_AGGRESSIVE:
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_set_integer(ctx, 16, level)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_target" takes ctx as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the target triple for compilation
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Free old target triple if any
    Let old_target be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 24)
    If old_target is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(old_target)
    End If

    If target is equal to 0:
        memory_set_pointer(ctx, 24, 0)
        Return 1
    End If

    Let new_target be string_duplicate(target)
    If new_target is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 24, new_target)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_verbose" takes ctx as Integer, verbose as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 64, verbose)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_debug_info" takes ctx as Integer, enabled as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 104, enabled)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_warning_level" takes ctx as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 112, level)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_incremental" takes ctx as Integer, enabled as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 72, enabled)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_link_output" takes ctx as Integer, enabled as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 136, enabled)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_executable_path" takes ctx as Integer, path as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let old_path be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 144)
    If old_path is not equal to 0:
        deallocate(old_path)
    End If

    If path is equal to 0:
        memory_set_pointer(ctx, 144, 0)
        Return 1
    End If

    Let new_path be string_duplicate(path)
    If new_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 144, new_path)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_set_parallel_count" takes ctx as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 184, count)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build Execution
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "build_compile_single_file" takes ctx as Integer, source_path as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compile a single source file using the compiler driver
    Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If source_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Determine output file path by replacing .runa extension with .s
    Let output_dir be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 8)
    If output_dir is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Output directory not set"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Extract the filename from the source path (find last '/')
    Let filename be source_path
    Let src_len be string_length(source_path)
    Let scan_idx be src_len minus 1
    While scan_idx is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let char_at be memory_get_byte(source_path, scan_idx)
        If char_at is equal to 47:  Note: '/' = ASCII 47
            Set filename to source_path plus scan_idx plus 1
            Set scan_idx to 0  Note: break out of loop
        End If
        Set scan_idx to scan_idx minus 1
    End While

    Note: Build output path: output_dir/filename with .runa replaced by .s
    Let filename_len be string_length(filename)
    Note: Check if filename ends with ".runa" (5 chars)
    Let base_name be filename
    Let base_len be filename_len
    If filename_len is greater than 5:
        Let ext_start be filename_len minus 5
        Let ext_char be memory_get_byte(filename, ext_start)
        If ext_char is equal to 46:  Note: '.' = ASCII 46
            Set base_len to ext_start
        End If
    End If

    Note: Construct output path: output_dir + "/" + base_name + ".s"
    Let path_temp1 be string_concat(output_dir, "/")
    Let arena be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 56)
    Let base_copy be arena_allocate(arena, base_len plus 1, 1)
    memory_copy(base_copy, filename, base_len)
    memory_set_byte(base_copy, base_len, 0)
    Let path_temp2 be string_concat(path_temp1, base_copy)
    deallocate(path_temp1)
    Let output_path be string_concat(path_temp2, ".s")
    deallocate(path_temp2)

    Let is_verbose be memory_get_integer(ctx, 64)
    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
        Let msg_temp be string_concat("[BUILD] Compiling: ", source_path)
        Let msg be string_concat(msg_temp, " -> ")
        deallocate(msg_temp)
        Let msg_final be string_concat(msg, output_path)
        deallocate(msg)
        Display msg_final
        deallocate(msg_final)
    End If

    Note: Read the source file
    Let source_content be runtime_read_file(source_path)
    If source_content is equal to 0:
        Let error_msg be string_concat("[BUILD ERROR] Could not read: ", source_path)
        Alert error_msg
        build_record_error(ctx, error_msg)
        deallocate(error_msg)
        deallocate(output_path)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create lexer for the source
    Let lexer be lexer_create(source_content)
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to create lexer"
        deallocate(source_content)
        deallocate(output_path)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create parser
    Let parser be parser_create(lexer)
    If parser is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to create parser"
        lexer_destroy(lexer)
        deallocate(source_content)
        deallocate(output_path)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse the source
    Let program be parser_parse_program(parser)
    If program is equal to 0:
        Set error_msg to string_concat("[BUILD ERROR] Parse failed: ", source_path)
        Alert error_msg
        build_record_error(ctx, error_msg)
        deallocate(error_msg)
        parser_destroy(parser)
        lexer_destroy(lexer)
        deallocate(source_content)
        deallocate(output_path)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Compile the program to assembly
    Let compile_result be compile_program(program, output_path)
    If compile_result is not equal to 0:
        Set error_msg to string_concat("[BUILD ERROR] Compilation failed: ", source_path)
        Alert error_msg
        build_record_error(ctx, error_msg)
        deallocate(error_msg)
        program_destroy(program)
        parser_destroy(parser)
        lexer_destroy(lexer)
        deallocate(source_content)
        deallocate(output_path)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Register the generated assembly file
    Let assembly_files be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 128)
    If assembly_files is not equal to 0:
        Let asm_path_copy be string_duplicate(output_path)
        arraylist_add(assembly_files, asm_path_copy)
    End If

    Note: Update compiled count
    Let compiled_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 32)
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 32, compiled_count plus 1)

    Note: Cleanup
    program_destroy(program)
    parser_destroy(parser)
    lexer_destroy(lexer)
    deallocate(source_content)
    deallocate(output_path)

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_all" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compile all registered source files sequentially
    Note: Returns BUILD_SUCCESS if all succeed, BUILD_FAILURE if any fail, BUILD_PARTIAL if some fail

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Build context is null"
        Return BUILD_FAILURE
    End If

    Note: Mark build as active
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 1)

    Note: Record start time
    Let arena be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 56)
    Let start_time be time_now_monotonic(arena)
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 88, start_time)

    Note: Reset counters
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 32, 0)  Note: compiled_count
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 40, 0)  Note: error_count

    Let source_files be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 0)
    If source_files is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Source files list is null"
        memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)
        Return BUILD_FAILURE
    End If

    Let file_count be arraylist_size(source_files)
    If file_count is equal to 0:
        Display "[BUILD] No source files to compile"
        memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)
        Return BUILD_SUCCESS
    End If

    Let is_verbose be memory_get_integer(ctx, 64)
    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
        Let count_str be integer_to_string(file_count)
        Let msg be string_concat("[BUILD] Compiling ", count_str)
        deallocate(count_str)
        Let msg2 be string_concat(msg, " source file(s)...")
        deallocate(msg)
        Display msg2
        deallocate(msg2)
    End If

    Note: Iterate through all source files and compile each one
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than file_count:
        Let source_path be arraylist_get(source_files, i)
        If source_path is not equal to 0:
            Let result be build_compile_single_file(ctx, source_path)
            If result is equal to 0:
                Note: Compilation failed for this file - record error count
                Let error_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 40)
                memory_set_integer(ctx, 40, error_count plus 1)
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Record end time
    Let end_time be time_now_monotonic(arena)
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 96, end_time)

    Note: Mark build as inactive
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)

    Note: Determine result
    Let compiled_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 32)
    Set error_count to memory_get_integer(ctx, 40)

    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
        Let compiled_str be integer_to_string(compiled_count)
        Let error_str be integer_to_string(error_count)
        Let msg1 be string_concat("[BUILD] Compiled: ", compiled_str)
        deallocate(compiled_str)
        Set msg2 to string_concat(msg1, " succeeded, ")
        deallocate(msg1)
        Let msg3 be string_concat(msg2, error_str)
        deallocate(error_str)
        deallocate(msg2)
        Let msg4 be string_concat(msg3, " failed")
        deallocate(msg3)
        Display msg4
        deallocate(msg4)
    End If

    If error_count is equal to 0:
        Return BUILD_SUCCESS
    End If

    If compiled_count is equal to 0:
        Return BUILD_FAILURE
    End If

    Return BUILD_PARTIAL
End Process

Process called "build_with_dependencies" takes ctx as Integer, dep_graph as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compile source files in topological order according to the dependency graph
    Note: dep_graph is a pointer to a DependencyGraph (from dependency_manager.runa)
    Note: Returns BUILD_SUCCESS, BUILD_FAILURE, or BUILD_PARTIAL

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Build context is null"
        Return BUILD_FAILURE
    End If

    If dep_graph is equal to 0:
        Note: No dependency graph provided, fall back to sequential build
        Display "[BUILD] No dependency graph provided, building sequentially"
        Return build_all(ctx)
    End If

    Note: Store the dependency graph reference
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 80, dep_graph)

    Note: Mark build as active
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 1)

    Note: Record start time
    Let arena be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 56)
    Let start_time be time_now_monotonic(arena)
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 88, start_time)

    Note: Reset counters
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 32, 0)
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 40, 0)

    Note: Get the topological build order from the dependency graph
    Note: get_build_order returns a pointer to an ArrayList of module name strings
    Let build_order be get_build_order(dep_graph)
    If build_order is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Failed to compute topological build order (possible cycle)"
        memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)
        Return BUILD_FAILURE
    End If

    Let order_count be arraylist_size(build_order)
    If order_count is equal to 0:
        Display "[BUILD] No modules in build order"
        memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)
        Return BUILD_SUCCESS
    End If

    Let is_verbose be memory_get_integer(ctx, 64)
    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
        Let count_str be integer_to_string(order_count)
        Let msg be string_concat("[BUILD] Building ", count_str)
        deallocate(count_str)
        Let msg2 be string_concat(msg, " module(s) in dependency order...")
        deallocate(msg)
        Display msg2
        deallocate(msg2)
    End If

    Note: Compile each module in topological order
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than order_count:
        Let module_name be arraylist_get(build_order, i)
        If module_name is not equal to 0:
            Note: Find the corresponding source file in our source files list
            Let source_path be build_find_source_for_module(ctx, module_name)
            If source_path is not equal to 0:
                Let result be build_compile_single_file(ctx, source_path)
                If result is equal to 0:
                    Let error_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 40)
                    memory_set_integer(ctx, 40, error_count plus 1)

                    Note: In dependency builds, a failure may cascade
                    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
                        Let err_msg be string_concat("[BUILD] Dependency build failed for module: ", module_name)
                        Alert err_msg
                        deallocate(err_msg)
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                If is_verbose is equal to 1:
                    Let warn_msg be string_concat("[BUILD WARNING] No source file found for module: ", module_name)
                    Display warn_msg
                    deallocate(warn_msg)
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Record end time
    Let end_time be time_now_monotonic(arena)
    memory_set_pointer(ctx, 96, end_time)

    Note: Mark build as inactive
    memory_set_integer(ctx, 160, 0)

    Note: Determine result
    Let compiled_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 32)
    Set error_count to memory_get_integer(ctx, 40)

    If error_count is equal to 0:
        Return BUILD_SUCCESS
    End If
    If compiled_count is equal to 0:
        Return BUILD_FAILURE
    End If
    Return BUILD_PARTIAL
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build Helper Functions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "build_find_source_for_module" takes ctx as Integer, module_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search the registered source files for one matching the given module name
    Note: Module name matching: a module "foo" matches "foo.runa", "path/to/foo.runa", etc.
    Note: Returns the source file path pointer, or 0 if not found

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If module_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_files be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 0)
    If source_files is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let module_runa be string_concat(module_name, ".runa")
    Let file_count be arraylist_size(source_files)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than file_count:
        Let source_path be arraylist_get(source_files, i)
        If source_path is not equal to 0:
            Note: Check if source_path ends with the module_runa filename
            Let ends_match be string_ends_with(source_path, module_runa)
            If ends_match is equal to 1:
                deallocate(module_runa)
                Return source_path
            End If

            Note: Also check exact match
            Let exact_match be string_equals(source_path, module_name)
            If exact_match is equal to 1:
                deallocate(module_runa)
                Return source_path
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    deallocate(module_runa)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "build_record_error" takes ctx as Integer, error_msg as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Record an error message into the build context error list
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If error_msg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let error_messages be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 48)
    If error_messages is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let msg_copy be string_duplicate(error_msg)
    If msg_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let result be arraylist_add(error_messages, msg_copy)
    If result is equal to 0:
        deallocate(msg_copy)
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "build_get_error_count" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return memory_get_integer(ctx, 40)
End Process

Process called "build_get_error_message" takes ctx as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the error message at the given index, or 0 if invalid
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let error_messages be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 48)
    If error_messages is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be arraylist_size(error_messages)
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to count:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return arraylist_get(error_messages, index)
End Process

Process called "build_get_compiled_count" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return memory_get_integer(ctx, 32)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build Reporting
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "build_print_summary" takes ctx as Integer returns Nothing:
    Note: Print a summary of the build results
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Alert "[BUILD ERROR] Cannot print summary: context is null"
        Return
    End If

    Display "============================================"
    Display "              BUILD SUMMARY"
    Display "============================================"

    Let compiled_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 32)
    Let error_count be memory_get_integer(ctx, 40)
    Let file_count be get_source_file_count(ctx)

    Let files_str be integer_to_string(file_count)
    Let msg1 be string_concat("  Source files:    ", files_str)
    deallocate(files_str)
    Display msg1
    deallocate(msg1)

    Let compiled_str be integer_to_string(compiled_count)
    Let msg2 be string_concat("  Compiled:        ", compiled_str)
    deallocate(compiled_str)
    Display msg2
    deallocate(msg2)

    Let error_str be integer_to_string(error_count)
    Let msg3 be string_concat("  Errors:          ", error_str)
    deallocate(error_str)
    Display msg3
    deallocate(msg3)

    Note: Print build duration if timing info is available
    Let start_time be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 88)
    Let end_time be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 96)
    If start_time is not equal to 0:
        If end_time is not equal to 0:
            Let arena be memory_get_pointer(ctx, 56)
            Let duration be time_diff(end_time, start_time, arena)
            Let duration_ms be time_to_milliseconds(duration)
            Let duration_str be integer_to_string(duration_ms)
            Let msg4 be string_concat("  Duration:        ", duration_str)
            deallocate(duration_str)
            Let msg5 be string_concat(msg4, " ms")
            deallocate(msg4)
            Display msg5
            deallocate(msg5)
        End If
    End If

    Let opt_level be memory_get_integer(ctx, 16)
    Let opt_str be integer_to_string(opt_level)
    Let msg6 be string_concat("  Optimization:    O", opt_str)
    deallocate(opt_str)
    Display msg6
    deallocate(msg6)

    Display "============================================"

    Note: Print errors if any
    If error_count is greater than 0:
        Display "  Errors:"
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than error_count:
            Let error_msg be build_get_error_message(ctx, i)
            If error_msg is not equal to 0:
                Let idx_str be integer_to_string(i plus 1)
                Let line be string_concat("    ", idx_str)
                deallocate(idx_str)
                Let line2 be string_concat(line, ". ")
                deallocate(line)
                Let line3 be string_concat(line2, error_msg)
                deallocate(line2)
                Display line3
                deallocate(line3)
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Display "============================================"
    End If
End Process
